<p>Example [5] poses a problem, though. â€˜Mustâ€™ in the sense of obligation doesnâ€™t have a past form. We simply use â€˜had toâ€™, thus:</p>

<p>[5.p] <em>Tom had to pay the rent yesterday.</em></p>

<h2 id="alas-the-land-of-regrets">Alas! The land of regrets</h2>

<p>Letâ€™s say Tom was a bit forgetful and didnâ€™t pay the rent even though he had to. To talk about regret over something that <strong>did not happen</strong>.</p>

